1
00:00:01,681 --> 00:00:03,681
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:00:36,681 --> 00:00:38,401
DOCTOR: I'm sure
it's somewhere around here.

3
00:00:38,521 --> 00:00:39,921
-(CHILDREN LAUGH)
-GRAHAM: Come on, Doc, admit it.

4
00:00:40,001 --> 00:00:41,281
I don't know what you mean.

5
00:00:41,361 --> 00:00:45,681
Well, look at it! This ain't
the coronation of Elizabeth I, is it?

6
00:00:45,761 --> 00:00:47,521
-Mmm.
-It's like a street party.

7
00:00:47,841 --> 00:00:50,001
Ye olde hipster pop-up happenin'.

8
00:00:50,561 --> 00:00:54,041
The TARDIS is being a bit stubborn
at exact readings.

9
00:00:54,841 --> 00:00:57,161
-So where are we?
-Apple bobbing!

10
00:00:57,401 --> 00:00:59,241
I love apple bobbing.

11
00:01:00,241 --> 00:01:02,561
-Is this Halloween?
-No, it's Sunday.

12
00:01:02,721 --> 00:01:03,961
Yeah, but what's the party for?

13
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:05,561
We do this every Sunday.

14
00:01:05,681 --> 00:01:07,121
Oh, happy Sunday.

15
00:01:07,401 --> 00:01:09,281
Northern accent,
we must be close to home.

16
00:01:09,561 --> 00:01:12,121
(HAND BELL RINGING)

17
00:01:15,361 --> 00:01:18,041
Mistress Savage demands your presence.

18
00:01:18,481 --> 00:01:20,441
The ceremony will begin.

19
00:01:20,561 --> 00:01:23,041
Anybody else missing the party vibe
all of a sudden?

20
00:01:23,761 --> 00:01:25,321
Go on.

21
00:01:41,641 --> 00:01:43,241
YASMIN: Where are they all going?

22
00:01:43,321 --> 00:01:45,361
Whatever this is,
I need you all to remember,

23
00:01:45,441 --> 00:01:47,881
the most important thing
about dips into the past,

24
00:01:48,601 --> 00:01:51,121
do not interfere
with the fundamental fabric of history.

25
00:01:51,561 --> 00:01:53,001
Even if something's not right?

26
00:01:53,521 --> 00:01:55,281
DOCTOR: Yep, and judging
by the vibe here,

27
00:01:55,361 --> 00:01:56,921
something is definitely not right.

28
00:01:57,041 --> 00:01:58,361
(GIRL SOBBING)

29
00:02:00,521 --> 00:02:01,601
Are you okay?

30
00:02:02,281 --> 00:02:04,281
Can you tell us what's going on here?

31
00:02:18,321 --> 00:02:20,361
Guys, that's Pendle Hill.

32
00:02:20,761 --> 00:02:22,241
We're in Lancashire.

33
00:02:23,281 --> 00:02:25,041
People of Bilehurst Cragg,

34
00:02:26,481 --> 00:02:29,161
we are forced to meet here once again.

35
00:02:30,561 --> 00:02:32,481
Satan stalks this land.

36
00:02:33,321 --> 00:02:35,441
We must continue to root him out

37
00:02:35,561 --> 00:02:39,881
and do whatever it takes
to save the soul of our village.

38
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:44,161
Let us put the accused to the test.

39
00:02:44,681 --> 00:02:47,241
-Granny!
-Hush, Willa.

40
00:02:47,801 --> 00:02:49,721
-It's a witch trial.
-BECKA: Old Mother Twiston.

41
00:02:49,801 --> 00:02:51,321
Must be early 17th century.

42
00:02:51,761 --> 00:02:54,121
You stand accused of witchcraft

43
00:02:54,881 --> 00:02:57,281
and shall be tried by my ducking stool,

44
00:02:57,801 --> 00:03:00,481
hewn from the mightiest tree
on Pendle Hill.

45
00:03:01,121 --> 00:03:04,041
If you drown, you are innocent.

46
00:03:04,641 --> 00:03:09,521
If you survive, you are a witch
and shall be hanged.

47
00:03:09,641 --> 00:03:10,881
(VILLAGERS CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY)

48
00:03:11,761 --> 00:03:13,081
This is way too dark for me.

49
00:03:13,361 --> 00:03:14,521
We've got to do something, Doctor.

50
00:03:14,641 --> 00:03:17,881
Uh-uh. The Doc said don't interfere.
You said don't interfere, right?

51
00:03:18,281 --> 00:03:19,321
MOTHER TWISTON: Don't cry, Willa.

52
00:03:19,561 --> 00:03:20,561
(WHIMPERS)

53
00:03:21,281 --> 00:03:22,961
I will still be with you.

54
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:27,721
I will still be with you.
In the water.

55
00:03:27,801 --> 00:03:28,801
In the fire.

56
00:03:29,441 --> 00:03:30,601
In the air.

57
00:03:31,361 --> 00:03:32,521
In the earth.

58
00:03:34,361 --> 00:03:35,521
-Duck the witch.
-(VILLAGERS SHOUTING)

59
00:03:35,881 --> 00:03:37,881
-Duck the witch!
-MAN: Duck the witch!

60
00:03:39,161 --> 00:03:40,401
YASMIN: Doctor!
WOMAN: Not that way.

61
00:03:40,561 --> 00:03:41,561
MAN 2: Witch!
MAN 3: Come on!

62
00:03:42,401 --> 00:03:43,841
-MAN 4: Duck the witch!
- (CLAMOURING)

63
00:03:46,161 --> 00:03:47,161
Granny!

64
00:03:47,241 --> 00:03:49,481
-MAN 5: That's it!
-Meet me on the other side.

65
00:03:50,081 --> 00:03:51,241
So much for not interfering.

66
00:03:51,441 --> 00:03:52,721
YASMIN: Open the bridge. Come on!

67
00:03:52,801 --> 00:03:54,641
BECKA: Who dares interfere
with this trial?

68
00:03:54,721 --> 00:03:58,161
Thirty-five witches we have tried,
and still Satan surrounds us.

69
00:03:58,361 --> 00:03:59,961
We shall not be stopped.

70
00:04:00,401 --> 00:04:02,041
(PANTING)

71
00:04:02,801 --> 00:04:03,801
YASMIN: Doctor, we're here.

72
00:04:04,241 --> 00:04:06,761
BECKA: You will be punished
for your interference.

73
00:04:06,921 --> 00:04:10,081
The trials are sacred.
They are the will of God!

74
00:04:10,321 --> 00:04:11,601
Is she alive?

75
00:04:18,161 --> 00:04:19,641
I'm sorry.

76
00:04:21,401 --> 00:04:22,601
-(SOBBING)
-BECKA: Now we have

77
00:04:22,681 --> 00:04:25,241
no way of knowing
if Mother Twiston was a witch or not.

78
00:04:26,201 --> 00:04:29,001
Guards, whip these wanderers
off this bank

79
00:04:29,081 --> 00:04:31,921
and then seize Willa Twiston.
We can take no chances.

80
00:04:32,321 --> 00:04:33,681
Leave her alone.

81
00:04:34,161 --> 00:04:36,161
I'd bet my life neither of these women
are witches.

82
00:04:36,241 --> 00:04:40,081
But you, Mistress Savage,
are without question, a murderer!

83
00:04:41,201 --> 00:04:43,481
Who are you to address me this way?

84
00:04:43,921 --> 00:04:45,761
I'll tell you who I am.

85
00:04:47,161 --> 00:04:48,321
Huh?

86
00:04:48,601 --> 00:04:50,361
Oh, sorry, one sec.

87
00:04:52,721 --> 00:04:54,041
Witchfinder General?

88
00:04:54,801 --> 00:04:57,681
That's right, Witchfinder General,

89
00:04:58,441 --> 00:05:01,121
with my crack team,
taking over this village.

90
00:05:01,201 --> 00:05:02,201
Right, gang?

91
00:05:04,281 --> 00:05:06,641
Yeah, 'cause you
are in Special Measures.

92
00:05:06,721 --> 00:05:08,881
DOCTOR: Now do you recognise
our authority?

93
00:05:11,161 --> 00:05:13,121
I do beg your pardon,
Mistress Witchfinder.

94
00:05:13,281 --> 00:05:16,441
Please come to my home.
We must talk in private.

95
00:05:17,561 --> 00:05:19,841
If you swear not to hurt that girl
or anyone else.

96
00:05:21,681 --> 00:05:24,161
If that is your wish,
you have the command.

97
00:05:27,401 --> 00:05:28,921
DOCTOR: Everybody go home.

98
00:05:30,001 --> 00:05:32,601
-This trial is over.
-(SOBS GENTLY)

99
00:05:37,241 --> 00:05:38,921
I have to bury her.

100
00:05:50,721 --> 00:05:51,921
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

101
00:05:52,081 --> 00:05:53,961
BECKA: Please forgive me, Mistress.

102
00:05:54,201 --> 00:05:55,321
If I'd have known who you were,

103
00:05:55,401 --> 00:05:57,361
I'd have bowed
to your authority immediately.

104
00:05:57,761 --> 00:06:01,041
So tell me, who exactly are you?
And what gives you authority here?

105
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:04,921
I am Becka Savage,
landowner of Bilehurst Cragg.

106
00:06:05,441 --> 00:06:08,361
It belonged to my late husband.
Passed to me when he died.

107
00:06:08,921 --> 00:06:10,601
I have tried to be a benevolent leader,

108
00:06:10,681 --> 00:06:14,601
but it's very difficult in these times,
especially for a woman.

109
00:06:15,361 --> 00:06:16,681
If you're the landowner,

110
00:06:17,721 --> 00:06:19,761
why are you walking?
Where are the horses?

111
00:06:21,401 --> 00:06:23,161
Horses are banned in Bilehurst.

112
00:06:24,401 --> 00:06:26,401
They are creatures of Satan.

113
00:06:27,201 --> 00:06:28,601
I had them all shot.

114
00:06:30,721 --> 00:06:32,201
Hey, Doc.

115
00:06:33,361 --> 00:06:35,441
I've done the old
Pendle Witches Walking Trail,

116
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:37,521
nobody ever mentioned Bilehurst Cragg.

117
00:06:37,801 --> 00:06:40,561
Never heard of it,
and she's killed 35 people.

118
00:06:40,641 --> 00:06:41,881
-Thirty-six, now.
-Yeah.

119
00:06:41,961 --> 00:06:43,761
Maybe she wipes this whole place
off the map?

120
00:06:43,961 --> 00:06:45,681
We're going to find out what happened.

121
00:06:45,801 --> 00:06:47,401
And how we can make her stop.

122
00:06:48,121 --> 00:06:49,961
And that hall looks like
the best place to start.

123
00:06:50,041 --> 00:06:51,481
YASMIN: Not the only place.

124
00:06:51,641 --> 00:06:53,441
I'm gonna find that girl
who's just lost her gran.

125
00:06:53,521 --> 00:06:56,321
We'll deal with Her Ladyship,
if you go do some family liaison.

126
00:06:56,481 --> 00:06:57,681
I'll meet you in a bit.

127
00:06:57,761 --> 00:06:59,601
Hopefully by then I'll be a bit dry.

128
00:07:08,641 --> 00:07:10,321
BECKA: I hope the fire has warmed you.

129
00:07:10,481 --> 00:07:12,081
-Some wine?
-No.

130
00:07:12,881 --> 00:07:15,681
So, your witch trials have become
a weekly event

131
00:07:15,761 --> 00:07:17,681
with a village celebration.

132
00:07:17,761 --> 00:07:21,241
Any moment where a witch is uncovered
and Satan driven out

133
00:07:21,321 --> 00:07:23,081
has to be cause for a celebration.

134
00:07:23,321 --> 00:07:25,321
We will not stop
until that work is done.

135
00:07:25,401 --> 00:07:29,161
You keep saying "Satan", but how
is Satan manifesting himself here?

136
00:07:30,081 --> 00:07:33,321
Blighting the crops. Bewitching animals.

137
00:07:33,401 --> 00:07:37,281
Plaguing people with fits,
sickness, and visions.

138
00:07:37,361 --> 00:07:40,201
If all that's Satan,
where do the witches come in to it?

139
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:44,481
They're in league with him.
Kill the witches, defeat Satan.

140
00:07:45,081 --> 00:07:47,521
As King James has written
in his new Bible,

141
00:07:47,641 --> 00:07:49,521
"Thou shalt not suffer a witch to live."

142
00:07:49,601 --> 00:07:51,001
In the Old Testament.

143
00:07:51,161 --> 00:07:54,401
There's a twist in the sequel, "Love
thy neighbour”, which is why we've come.

144
00:07:54,881 --> 00:07:57,281
To help you fix your problems
without killing anyone.

145
00:07:58,041 --> 00:07:59,401
That's what King James would want.

146
00:08:00,321 --> 00:08:01,321
(GASPS)

147
00:08:01,801 --> 00:08:03,321
BECKA: What is the meaning of this?

148
00:08:03,761 --> 00:08:06,281
Madam, I have come to your rescue.

149
00:08:07,881 --> 00:08:08,881
King James. (GASPS)

150
00:08:08,961 --> 00:08:11,121
-(GASPS)
-Your Majesty.

151
00:08:11,201 --> 00:08:13,761
KING JAMES: You may
prostrate yourselves before me,

152
00:08:14,721 --> 00:08:18,641
God's chosen ruler
and Satan's greatest foe,

153
00:08:18,961 --> 00:08:23,721
come to vanquish the scourge
of witchcraft across the land.

154
00:08:24,561 --> 00:08:28,761
Forgive the mask, I have enemies
everywhere and have to travel incognito.

155
00:08:28,841 --> 00:08:31,241
Also, I rather like the drama.
(CHUCKLES)

156
00:08:31,321 --> 00:08:32,481
(LAUGHS)

157
00:08:32,721 --> 00:08:35,601
-(DOOR OPENS)
-A peculiar rag-bag of folks.

158
00:08:36,081 --> 00:08:38,681
And those garments... Are you actors?

159
00:08:39,161 --> 00:08:40,241
We are

160
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:44,121
witchfinders, Sire,
as we explained to Mistress Savage.

161
00:08:45,121 --> 00:08:46,921
Witchfinder's assistant?

162
00:08:47,881 --> 00:08:50,081
So you must be the Witchfinder General?

163
00:08:50,521 --> 00:08:52,601
-(GROANS)
-No, she said she was.

164
00:08:52,681 --> 00:08:55,561
(SCOFFING) A woman could never
be the general!

165
00:08:55,761 --> 00:08:59,001
(CHUCKLES HALF-HEARTEDLY)
Silly me, must have got all confused.

166
00:08:59,081 --> 00:09:00,601
-Mmm.
-DOCTOR: Mustn't I, boss?

167
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:03,681
Er, yeah, that's me, Sire.

168
00:09:03,761 --> 00:09:05,841
Er, Northwest Division,
promoted from Essex.

169
00:09:06,161 --> 00:09:07,521
And these are your underlings?

170
00:09:09,481 --> 00:09:13,481
It's a very flat team structure.
We all have our area of expertise.

171
00:09:13,561 --> 00:09:15,201
Even the wee lassie?

172
00:09:15,961 --> 00:09:18,241
Even me. Very handy under cover.

173
00:09:18,601 --> 00:09:19,961
Set a woman to catch a woman.

174
00:09:20,601 --> 00:09:25,801
A cunning ruse using your innate
aptitude for nosiness and gossip.

175
00:09:26,761 --> 00:09:27,761
(GROANS)

176
00:09:27,841 --> 00:09:32,601
And what is your field of expertise,
my Nubian prince?

177
00:09:32,841 --> 00:09:33,841
Er...

178
00:09:35,721 --> 00:09:36,721
Torture?

179
00:09:37,121 --> 00:09:38,361
-Me?
-KING JAMES: Yeah.

180
00:09:38,681 --> 00:09:39,761
Er...

181
00:09:40,721 --> 00:09:42,201
Paperwork, mostly, Your Majesty.

182
00:09:42,361 --> 00:09:44,201
Paper? How fascinating!

183
00:09:45,201 --> 00:09:46,241
We should talk.

184
00:09:46,921 --> 00:09:51,201
But first, madam, word has reached
me of your battle against Satan,

185
00:09:51,281 --> 00:09:53,441
your crusade against witchcraft.

186
00:09:53,721 --> 00:09:56,001
But what I saw today convinced me
you need assistance.

187
00:09:56,361 --> 00:09:57,521
That's what we've just been saying.

188
00:09:57,721 --> 00:09:58,881
Hold your tongue, lassie.

189
00:09:58,961 --> 00:10:01,161
Stick to snooping and leave the strategy
to your king.

190
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:03,001
This is no time for the weak.

191
00:10:03,081 --> 00:10:06,161
Satan preys on the innocent,
even while they sleep.

192
00:10:06,561 --> 00:10:10,081
Together, we must purify your land,

193
00:10:10,681 --> 00:10:13,921
starting with the grandchild
of the witch you tried today.

194
00:10:14,441 --> 00:10:15,761
A fine plan, is it not?

195
00:10:16,001 --> 00:10:18,041
-(GASPING)
-A genius plan, Your Majesty.

196
00:10:18,321 --> 00:10:20,041
-Oh.
-Together we shall save the souls

197
00:10:20,121 --> 00:10:21,921
of my people from Satan,

198
00:10:22,561 --> 00:10:24,441
even if it means killing them all.

199
00:10:24,761 --> 00:10:25,921
(GASPS)

200
00:10:32,881 --> 00:10:34,521
(WILLA SNIFFLES)

201
00:10:35,561 --> 00:10:36,761
WILLA: I will still be with you.

202
00:10:38,681 --> 00:10:40,041
In the water.

203
00:10:41,161 --> 00:10:42,161
In the fire.

204
00:10:45,481 --> 00:10:46,561
In the earth.

205
00:10:48,561 --> 00:10:49,561
In the air.

206
00:10:50,801 --> 00:10:51,801
Willa!

207
00:10:53,601 --> 00:10:54,601
(GASPING)

208
00:10:55,601 --> 00:10:57,081
Get away from her!

209
00:10:59,801 --> 00:11:00,881
(YASMIN GRUNTS)

210
00:11:01,921 --> 00:11:04,321
-Are you all right?
-What was that?

211
00:11:04,801 --> 00:11:06,081
I don't know.

212
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:09,201
But I want to help.

213
00:11:09,841 --> 00:11:12,361
You can't. Nobody can.

214
00:11:13,281 --> 00:11:15,201
Wait, Willa!

215
00:11:17,161 --> 00:11:18,601
Becka wasn't kidding.

216
00:11:19,561 --> 00:11:21,041
These are hard times for women.

217
00:11:22,401 --> 00:11:25,601
If we're not being drowned,
we're being patronised to death.

218
00:11:26,881 --> 00:11:28,321
(GASPS)

219
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:30,601
-(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)
-Becka's bedroom. In here, quick.

220
00:11:30,921 --> 00:11:32,401
We are gonna
help them though, right, Doc?

221
00:11:32,521 --> 00:11:34,961
I mean, otherwise this place
won't exist by the morning.

222
00:11:35,121 --> 00:11:38,161
Not now those two have hit it off,
I don't know which one's more barking.

223
00:11:43,241 --> 00:11:45,441
A dozen hankies. That's a lot.

224
00:11:46,121 --> 00:11:47,521
Maybe she cries herself to sleep.

225
00:11:48,481 --> 00:11:50,121
Maybe. Don't worry, Graham,

226
00:11:50,201 --> 00:11:52,401
I'm staying here and sorting it,
even if I am just a woman.

227
00:11:52,761 --> 00:11:55,201
Well, to be fair to King James,
you are snooping.

228
00:11:56,001 --> 00:11:57,281
I'm investigating!

229
00:11:58,681 --> 00:12:00,801
-Hey, missed a bit.
-(SNIFFS)

230
00:12:02,801 --> 00:12:03,801
Whoa.

231
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:05,721
This Becka's seriously paranoid, man.

232
00:12:06,081 --> 00:12:07,601
-(ALL GASP)
-Here you are!

233
00:12:07,921 --> 00:12:09,561
I've been creeping around this place
looking for you.

234
00:12:09,641 --> 00:12:12,521
I found that girl Willa at her granny's
grave, doing some kind of ritual,

235
00:12:12,681 --> 00:12:13,761
and the next thing I know,

236
00:12:13,881 --> 00:12:17,241
this big, kind of, mud tendril thing
attacked her!

237
00:12:17,361 --> 00:12:18,721
-"Mud tendril"?
-Coming up out of the ground.

238
00:12:18,801 --> 00:12:21,081
I had to smash it to pieces.
Got it all over me.

239
00:12:21,161 --> 00:12:22,801
Just the one mud tendril? How big?

240
00:12:22,961 --> 00:12:24,761
Oh, and when you say "ritual”,
do you mean like a spell?

241
00:12:24,841 --> 00:12:26,681
-Like she conjured it up?
-She was scared of it.

242
00:12:26,801 --> 00:12:29,681
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-Whatever it was, it wasn't friendly.

243
00:12:29,881 --> 00:12:31,241
-(BLEEPING)
-Just seems to be like

244
00:12:31,321 --> 00:12:32,761
good old-fashioned Lancashire mud.

245
00:12:33,521 --> 00:12:36,321
Here's the plan. You and me need
to check out that mud and talk to Willa.

246
00:12:36,721 --> 00:12:38,681
You two, stick with Becka
and King James,

247
00:12:38,801 --> 00:12:41,201
keep them here.
Make sure they don't kill anyone else.

248
00:12:41,281 --> 00:12:42,801
-King James?
-It's a long story.

249
00:12:43,041 --> 00:12:44,281
I'll explain on the way.

250
00:12:44,641 --> 00:12:46,521
Remember, no more witch hunts.

251
00:12:49,081 --> 00:12:51,681
KING JAMES: This is Alfonso,
my personal guardian.

252
00:12:51,761 --> 00:12:54,721
He guards my witch-finding tools
with his life.

253
00:12:55,121 --> 00:12:57,521
Time is against us
if we are to get to the village

254
00:12:57,601 --> 00:12:59,241
and hunt down the witches
from their hiding.

255
00:12:59,401 --> 00:13:00,441
No!

256
00:13:00,521 --> 00:13:02,441
(CHUCKLES) No, we're fine.

257
00:13:02,841 --> 00:13:05,241
I bet you have all the best kit,
Your Majesty.

258
00:13:05,401 --> 00:13:07,121
I have a great many artefacts.

259
00:13:07,721 --> 00:13:10,921
Torture implements, charms,
and a wide selection of body parts.

260
00:13:11,001 --> 00:13:12,001
Oh.

261
00:13:12,801 --> 00:13:13,801
Here.

262
00:13:14,761 --> 00:13:17,201
Belonged to my first
Witchfinder General.

263
00:13:17,361 --> 00:13:19,001
-Oh.
-KING JAMES: Scottie,

264
00:13:19,121 --> 00:13:21,001
who saved my life in Berwick,

265
00:13:21,241 --> 00:13:23,441
then later betrayed me,
so I had him shot.

266
00:13:25,321 --> 00:13:26,881
I'm sure you will serve me better.

267
00:13:27,481 --> 00:13:28,561
You may wear the hat.

268
00:13:28,721 --> 00:13:29,721
(CHUCKLES)

269
00:13:31,521 --> 00:13:32,521
You can trust me, Sire.

270
00:13:32,721 --> 00:13:33,961
I can trust no one.

271
00:13:34,521 --> 00:13:35,641
That is why I need all these.

272
00:13:36,281 --> 00:13:37,281
Mmm.

273
00:13:39,521 --> 00:13:41,001
To ward off evil spirits.

274
00:13:41,081 --> 00:13:42,081
Mmm.

275
00:13:43,001 --> 00:13:44,361
I'll be keeping an eye on you.

276
00:13:44,641 --> 00:13:45,641
(CHUCKLING EXCITEDLY)

277
00:13:45,721 --> 00:13:46,961
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY) What's this?

278
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:49,601
Careful, it's my pricker.

279
00:13:50,961 --> 00:13:52,241
Essential for inspections.

280
00:13:52,681 --> 00:13:55,761
A true witch will not bleed
if her mark is pricked.

281
00:13:56,761 --> 00:13:58,121
Madam, do you have one of these?

282
00:13:58,841 --> 00:13:59,961
-No, Sire.
-Hmm.

283
00:14:00,401 --> 00:14:02,321
You may use this. It's my spare.

284
00:14:02,561 --> 00:14:04,121
GRAHAM: (WHISPERING) Ryan, do something.

285
00:14:05,001 --> 00:14:09,721
Oh, erm, there's still some
really, really fascinating

286
00:14:10,321 --> 00:14:13,521
body parts in here
that you could tell us about.

287
00:14:14,321 --> 00:14:15,321
(MOUTHING)

288
00:14:15,441 --> 00:14:17,201
-Yes, perhaps later. (CHUCKLES)
-Mmm.

289
00:14:18,561 --> 00:14:21,201
Oh, but also, before we depart,

290
00:14:21,601 --> 00:14:24,641
we should make a list
of all the villagers.

291
00:14:24,761 --> 00:14:27,401
-Mmm.
-And names of suspects,

292
00:14:27,481 --> 00:14:29,521
background info.
It's all in the preparation.

293
00:14:29,641 --> 00:14:30,721
Well, there is no need.

294
00:14:30,801 --> 00:14:33,281
I know everything about this place
and my people.

295
00:14:33,481 --> 00:14:35,361
And I know everything about Satan.

296
00:14:35,761 --> 00:14:38,881
Together, we will find where he's hiding
and cut him out.

297
00:14:42,121 --> 00:14:43,241
By nightfall,

298
00:14:44,001 --> 00:14:47,801
every last witch in this village
shall be destroyed.

299
00:14:51,161 --> 00:14:52,161
YASMIN: Willa.

300
00:14:53,681 --> 00:14:55,641
My name's Yaz. This is the Doctor.

301
00:14:56,881 --> 00:14:57,881
Where are you going?

302
00:14:57,961 --> 00:14:59,321
As far away from here as I can.

303
00:14:59,641 --> 00:15:00,801
Don't blame you.

304
00:15:01,041 --> 00:15:03,841
But before you do,
can we talk to you first?

305
00:15:04,441 --> 00:15:05,521
We're not witchfinders,

306
00:15:05,761 --> 00:15:07,881
we just want to find out
exactly what's going on here

307
00:15:07,961 --> 00:15:09,241
and maybe we can fix things.

308
00:15:10,081 --> 00:15:12,641
Can you help us, Willa?
Because we want to help you.

309
00:15:15,601 --> 00:15:16,961
(GASPS)

310
00:15:17,161 --> 00:15:19,801
Wow! Are these all yours?

311
00:15:20,161 --> 00:15:21,161
They were my grandmother's.

312
00:15:21,601 --> 00:15:23,521
She made medicines to help people.

313
00:15:23,961 --> 00:15:25,241
She wasn't a witch.

314
00:15:25,961 --> 00:15:27,041
Everyone knows that.

315
00:15:27,601 --> 00:15:29,641
So why did Becka Savage target her?

316
00:15:29,921 --> 00:15:32,081
Maybe she was ashamed
of the woman who brought her up.

317
00:15:32,561 --> 00:15:34,201
Wait, you and Becka are family?

318
00:15:34,841 --> 00:15:35,881
Cousins.

319
00:15:36,401 --> 00:15:38,561
We were all close,
until Becka married up.

320
00:15:38,921 --> 00:15:41,241
(INHALES SHARPLY) Left us all behind.

321
00:15:42,641 --> 00:15:45,241
Still, thought it'd be safe
when the witch-hunt started.

322
00:15:46,281 --> 00:15:49,561
And then it just got worse and worse,
everyone turned on each other.

323
00:15:50,321 --> 00:15:53,001
Granny said it was only a matter of time
before they turned on us.

324
00:15:56,881 --> 00:15:58,001
I didn't believe her.

325
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:01,601
GRAHAM: Oi, oi, hold up.
What's the rush?

326
00:16:01,681 --> 00:16:03,041
I want this over

327
00:16:03,161 --> 00:16:06,961
so we can return to the way things were
before Satan infested this land.

328
00:16:07,561 --> 00:16:10,281
Excuse me, when you say "Satan”,
what exactly do you mean?

329
00:16:10,841 --> 00:16:13,961
Satan is all around us, all of the time.

330
00:16:14,321 --> 00:16:16,521
We must be strong
or else he will take us.

331
00:16:16,601 --> 00:16:17,881
Of that, I have no doubt.

332
00:16:18,401 --> 00:16:20,401
Really, no doubt?
What if you're wrong?

333
00:16:20,881 --> 00:16:23,481
Because you're killing
all these people, friends, neighbours.

334
00:16:23,601 --> 00:16:26,481
If people are good,
they have nothing to fear.

335
00:16:28,881 --> 00:16:30,601
Are you a good person, Mistress Savage?

336
00:16:33,161 --> 00:16:34,561
My conscience is clean.

337
00:16:35,081 --> 00:16:36,081
WILLA: Here.

338
00:16:36,241 --> 00:16:37,721
Granny's special tea.

339
00:16:38,361 --> 00:16:39,801
It soothes the soul.

340
00:16:41,161 --> 00:16:42,601
Unless you think I'm a witch.

341
00:16:50,881 --> 00:16:51,881
Are you not having any?

342
00:16:52,201 --> 00:16:53,321
I feel too sick.

343
00:16:55,201 --> 00:16:56,521
Do you mind if I check you over?

344
00:16:56,601 --> 00:16:58,361
Don't worry, I am a doctor.

345
00:16:58,881 --> 00:17:00,161
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-What's that?

346
00:17:00,241 --> 00:17:02,241
Er, specialist equipment.

347
00:17:05,001 --> 00:17:06,401
That movement in the mud,

348
00:17:06,481 --> 00:17:08,041
it was Satan, wasn't it?

349
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:09,801
-Doubt it.
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

350
00:17:09,921 --> 00:17:11,601
Not a big believer in Satan.

351
00:17:12,361 --> 00:17:14,481
My granny used to say
there was enough wonder in nature

352
00:17:14,601 --> 00:17:16,241
-without making things up.
-(BLEEPING)

353
00:17:16,361 --> 00:17:17,361
I like your granny.

354
00:17:18,721 --> 00:17:19,921
Completely normal.

355
00:17:20,641 --> 00:17:23,521
No magic, and no signs of any sickness.

356
00:17:23,801 --> 00:17:24,801
You're wrong.

357
00:17:25,081 --> 00:17:27,081
I think I know what it is
that's making you sick.

358
00:17:27,441 --> 00:17:29,521
I had it at my school where I'm from.

359
00:17:29,961 --> 00:17:32,001
When Izzy Flint
turned the whole class against me.

360
00:17:33,121 --> 00:17:35,161
Every day I'd wake up feeling this...

361
00:17:36,121 --> 00:17:37,121
Dread.

362
00:17:38,201 --> 00:17:39,201
Fear.

363
00:17:40,001 --> 00:17:42,281
-How did you get rid of it?
-YASMIN: I didn't.

364
00:17:43,321 --> 00:17:45,641
I just took it. Had the year from hell.

365
00:17:47,241 --> 00:17:50,881
When I say "hell", I don't literally
mean hell. I mean it was really awful.

366
00:17:51,081 --> 00:17:52,761
And I told myself when I got bigger,

367
00:17:53,161 --> 00:17:55,201
I'd stand up to the Izzy Flints
of this world.

368
00:17:55,441 --> 00:17:58,961
I can't stand up to Becka.
She'll have me tried for a witch.

369
00:18:01,241 --> 00:18:02,481
(SOFTLY) What am I meant to do?

370
00:18:03,401 --> 00:18:05,481
Seems to me like you have two choices.

371
00:18:06,201 --> 00:18:08,681
Run as far away from here as possible,

372
00:18:08,881 --> 00:18:10,361
or stick with us.

373
00:18:10,481 --> 00:18:13,241
We'll stand up to Becka Savage
and we'll make this place safe again.

374
00:18:13,441 --> 00:18:14,441
How would we do that?

375
00:18:14,601 --> 00:18:16,801
Ah! "We", that's good, Willa!

376
00:18:17,441 --> 00:18:18,801
See? Feels better already.

377
00:18:18,921 --> 00:18:21,721
Now, first things first,
I need to get a sample of that mud.

378
00:18:22,121 --> 00:18:23,241
Oh, can I use this?

379
00:18:24,801 --> 00:18:25,801
Oh, yeah.

380
00:18:26,641 --> 00:18:27,681
Want to come with us?

381
00:18:29,721 --> 00:18:30,721
Not really.

382
00:18:31,721 --> 00:18:35,121
Look at him, Alfonso's loyalty
is rare and pure,

383
00:18:35,201 --> 00:18:38,681
it's only a matter of time
before I inevitably get let down.

384
00:18:38,961 --> 00:18:40,641
Why do you find it so hard
to trust people?

385
00:18:40,761 --> 00:18:41,961
Mmm.

386
00:18:42,081 --> 00:18:44,161
It's a long, sad story.

387
00:18:44,721 --> 00:18:45,921
A tragedy. (LAUGHS)

388
00:18:46,441 --> 00:18:48,441
I've got time. Tell me.

389
00:18:52,361 --> 00:18:55,001
My father died when I was a baby.

390
00:18:55,281 --> 00:18:56,481
I feel you.

391
00:18:56,881 --> 00:18:59,161
I lost me mum and me nan.

392
00:19:00,801 --> 00:19:05,561
My father was murdered by my mother,
who was then imprisoned and beheaded.

393
00:19:07,081 --> 00:19:08,721
Okay, that's worse. Yeah.

394
00:19:08,841 --> 00:19:10,521
I was raised by regents.

395
00:19:11,081 --> 00:19:13,041
One was assassinated, one died in battle

396
00:19:13,161 --> 00:19:16,601
and another died
in suspicious circumstances.

397
00:19:17,641 --> 00:19:21,481
There have been numerous attempts
to kidnap me, kill me, or blow me up.

398
00:19:21,561 --> 00:19:22,841
It's a miracle I'm still alive.

399
00:19:22,921 --> 00:19:23,921
(LAUGHS)

400
00:19:26,121 --> 00:19:27,601
(CLEARS THROAT) You're not kidding.

401
00:19:28,401 --> 00:19:29,681
No, I'm not.

402
00:19:30,761 --> 00:19:35,561
It is a miracle that I have prevailed
whilst all around me, others fall.

403
00:19:36,841 --> 00:19:39,201
You should definitely get yourself
back to London, Sire.

404
00:19:40,081 --> 00:19:41,081
Keep yourself safe.

405
00:19:41,521 --> 00:19:43,721
God will keep me safe

406
00:19:44,481 --> 00:19:46,201
as long as I do his work.

407
00:19:46,881 --> 00:19:48,041
(INHALES DEEPLY)

408
00:19:48,441 --> 00:19:50,081
(EXHALES) Ooh!

409
00:19:50,481 --> 00:19:51,481
That felt good.

410
00:19:51,641 --> 00:19:52,681
(JAMES CHUCKLES)

411
00:19:53,241 --> 00:19:54,241
Thank you.

412
00:19:54,721 --> 00:19:57,561
And now we can have some fun.
Eh, Ryan?

413
00:19:59,601 --> 00:20:00,601
Just mud.

414
00:20:00,721 --> 00:20:02,721
No sign of any tendency to tendril.

415
00:20:03,121 --> 00:20:04,841
Shouldn't be disappointed,
but I am a bit.

416
00:20:06,241 --> 00:20:07,561
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

417
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:10,641
What was that ritual you were doing
before the tendril arrived?

418
00:20:10,961 --> 00:20:12,081
A prayer

419
00:20:12,401 --> 00:20:14,001
to help my grandmother rest in peace.

420
00:20:14,441 --> 00:20:18,241
I brought her body here,
I dug that grave and placed her in it.

421
00:20:18,681 --> 00:20:20,561
But I didn't get to finish the prayer.

422
00:20:20,721 --> 00:20:23,041
-You can finish it now if you like.
-Yes.

423
00:20:23,721 --> 00:20:25,041
DOCTOR: Right, little sample.

424
00:20:26,201 --> 00:20:27,481
What aren't you telling me?

425
00:20:27,881 --> 00:20:31,201
Whoa! I am no longer disappointed.

426
00:20:31,401 --> 00:20:33,081
See? The mud is alive!

427
00:20:33,161 --> 00:20:34,961
But now I'm not sure it's mud at all.

428
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:36,601
YASMIN: It looks pretty angry in there.

429
00:20:36,761 --> 00:20:38,201
-WILLA: Yaz?
-Obviously doesn't like

430
00:20:38,281 --> 00:20:40,441
being trapped, do you? What are you?

431
00:20:41,121 --> 00:20:42,401
Give us a clue.

432
00:20:42,801 --> 00:20:43,801
What's happening?

433
00:20:43,961 --> 00:20:45,441
I think this is some kind
of alien matter.

434
00:20:45,521 --> 00:20:47,201
But I'm not sure if it's sentient.

435
00:20:47,481 --> 00:20:48,481
Doctor,

436
00:20:49,241 --> 00:20:51,161
-park that, please.
-Why?

437
00:20:58,081 --> 00:20:59,081
Granny!

438
00:20:59,641 --> 00:21:01,921
-That is not your granny, Willa.
-Yes, it is.

439
00:21:02,361 --> 00:21:04,041
No, that's the not-mud.

440
00:21:04,201 --> 00:21:07,521
(PANTING) Some sort of alien matter
filling her body

441
00:21:07,601 --> 00:21:08,921
and reanimating it.

442
00:21:09,241 --> 00:21:10,761
So, it is pretty sentient.

443
00:21:10,921 --> 00:21:12,161
I'm so sorry for this, Willa.

444
00:21:12,681 --> 00:21:14,681
Hi, not-Willa's-granny.

445
00:21:15,121 --> 00:21:17,761
I presume you're just using the body
to give whatever you are, form.

446
00:21:17,961 --> 00:21:20,081
Better than tendrils, right?
But really not right.

447
00:21:20,561 --> 00:21:21,801
Not cool.

448
00:21:21,881 --> 00:21:23,201
Is that why it went after Willa?

449
00:21:23,481 --> 00:21:24,641
Of course.

450
00:21:25,321 --> 00:21:27,281
Not to kill her, but to fill her.

451
00:21:27,561 --> 00:21:29,681
Ooh, check out my rhymes.
Poetry under pressure.

452
00:21:29,761 --> 00:21:30,761
Oh.

453
00:21:30,881 --> 00:21:32,401
-(GURGLING)
-What are you doing?

454
00:21:32,801 --> 00:21:33,801
You want this?

455
00:21:34,761 --> 00:21:36,641
-One of you, is it? Or part of you?
-(GRUNTS)

456
00:21:36,761 --> 00:21:39,001
Oh, no, no, no! Not until you tell me
what's going on here.

457
00:21:39,481 --> 00:21:41,921
(GROANS IN DISGUST)
I don't like the look of your hands.

458
00:21:42,241 --> 00:21:44,801
It's all bubbling away inside you,
isn't it?

459
00:21:45,321 --> 00:21:46,961
-(GURGLING)
-Oh, no! You're not filling me!

460
00:21:47,761 --> 00:21:50,121
If you're that desperate for it, here.
Have it.

461
00:21:50,361 --> 00:21:52,201
(SLURPING AND MOANING)

462
00:21:52,841 --> 00:21:53,881
Delightful.

463
00:21:54,521 --> 00:21:55,521
Down the hatch.

464
00:21:56,201 --> 00:21:57,841
I've got so many questions
right now, like,

465
00:21:57,921 --> 00:21:59,481
did you drink that or absorb it?

466
00:21:59,801 --> 00:22:02,281
Are you all one big muddy mass,
or separate entities

467
00:22:02,521 --> 00:22:03,721
only taking the one body?

468
00:22:04,081 --> 00:22:05,081
Doctor?

469
00:22:07,521 --> 00:22:09,921
DOCTOR: Oh.
Always good to get fast answers.

470
00:22:10,321 --> 00:22:11,801
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

471
00:22:12,841 --> 00:22:13,841
What was that?

472
00:22:14,041 --> 00:22:15,241
I cannot imagine.

473
00:22:15,481 --> 00:22:17,721
Erm, best let us deal with that, Sire.

474
00:22:17,841 --> 00:22:19,561
You should stay here
where it's safe, Sire.

475
00:22:19,641 --> 00:22:21,001
Nowhere is safe

476
00:22:22,081 --> 00:22:24,361
until Satan has been vanquished.

477
00:22:24,441 --> 00:22:25,721
GRAHAM: Oh, did it come
from that way, Sire?

478
00:22:25,801 --> 00:22:26,841
I thought it came from the other way.

479
00:22:26,961 --> 00:22:28,601
-DOCTOR: No! Stay back, please!
-Come on.

480
00:22:28,721 --> 00:22:30,681
I've given you the blob,
what more do you need?

481
00:22:31,441 --> 00:22:32,841
It's so annoying when they're silent.

482
00:22:32,921 --> 00:22:34,001
KING JAMES: Witchcraft!

483
00:22:34,081 --> 00:22:35,321
So much for keeping
that lot at the house.

484
00:22:35,401 --> 00:22:36,521
KING JAMES: Stay where you are!

485
00:22:36,601 --> 00:22:38,201
-Hi, Sire! I know it looks bad.
-Uh...

486
00:22:38,321 --> 00:22:40,121
But don't worry, I'm all over it.

487
00:22:40,361 --> 00:22:42,561
Willa Twiston was the witch all along!

488
00:22:42,921 --> 00:22:46,081
-I knew it!
-I'm not. This isn't me, Becka! I swear!

489
00:22:46,201 --> 00:22:48,401
She's right.
It's not her and it's not witchcraft.

490
00:22:48,561 --> 00:22:50,201
-I'm working it out.
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)

491
00:22:50,281 --> 00:22:51,561
KING JAMES: This is beyond you!

492
00:22:51,721 --> 00:22:54,241
-Alfonso, shoot them!
-Of course, Your Majesty.

493
00:22:54,401 --> 00:22:55,801
No, Alfonso, don't.

494
00:22:56,201 --> 00:22:58,561
In the air and in the earth!

495
00:22:59,161 --> 00:23:01,161
-(YELPS)
-(ALL GASP)

496
00:23:02,441 --> 00:23:03,641
KING JAMES: Alfonso.

497
00:23:03,761 --> 00:23:05,881
Now you've made them angry.
They're getting stronger.

498
00:23:06,481 --> 00:23:07,641
Everybody out of here.

499
00:23:07,801 --> 00:23:09,041
-(WHIMPERS)
-YASMIN: Get away from them now!

500
00:23:09,121 --> 00:23:11,481
BECKA: We must protect you, Sire.
Back through the forest.

501
00:23:12,921 --> 00:23:14,041
DOCTOR: Keep running.

502
00:23:16,281 --> 00:23:18,081
This clearing, through here.

503
00:23:18,441 --> 00:23:19,641
(JAMES WHIMPERS)

504
00:23:19,761 --> 00:23:21,041
I don't think they're following.

505
00:23:21,121 --> 00:23:24,121
(PANTING) If they're not following,
what are they doing?

506
00:23:24,201 --> 00:23:25,241
Want us to go and look?

507
00:23:25,521 --> 00:23:28,521
We escaped from Satan and you wish
to go directly back into battle?

508
00:23:28,601 --> 00:23:31,601
We need to know what they're up to.
Make sure no one else is in danger.

509
00:23:31,721 --> 00:23:34,641
I'll go too and keep an eye
on my underlings.

510
00:23:34,721 --> 00:23:36,561
-Very well.
-DOCTOR: I'll stay with Willa.

511
00:23:36,801 --> 00:23:37,921
Be careful!

512
00:23:38,761 --> 00:23:39,961
What were those aberrations?

513
00:23:40,121 --> 00:23:43,081
-It is the work of Satan!
-It wasn't Satan.

514
00:23:43,201 --> 00:23:45,081
Or witches, or Willa's granny.

515
00:23:45,161 --> 00:23:48,281
Those creatures were being controlled
by something in the mud.

516
00:23:48,521 --> 00:23:50,041
Something not of this Earth.

517
00:23:50,121 --> 00:23:52,641
Something beyond your understanding.

518
00:23:53,241 --> 00:23:54,481
Something from hell?

519
00:23:54,561 --> 00:23:56,081
More like from the heavens.

520
00:23:56,761 --> 00:23:58,641
It chose to kill Alfonso
when he was a threat.

521
00:23:58,721 --> 00:24:02,441
But in other circumstances, it fills
the bodies and uses them as vessels.

522
00:24:02,921 --> 00:24:04,841
I don't know why.
Maybe only when they're dead.

523
00:24:04,921 --> 00:24:06,761
No. It attacked me, too.

524
00:24:06,841 --> 00:24:07,841
DOCTOR: And why today?

525
00:24:08,121 --> 00:24:09,321
Because this is my problem.

526
00:24:09,521 --> 00:24:12,001
I can buy that this is the biggest ever
witch-hunt in England,

527
00:24:12,161 --> 00:24:14,801
or I can buy it's an alien mud invasion.

528
00:24:14,921 --> 00:24:17,241
But both on the same day?
I can't buy that!

529
00:24:17,321 --> 00:24:18,961
Why does the lassie speak of commerce?

530
00:24:19,041 --> 00:24:20,241
-DOCTOR: Oh, wait.
-I don't know.

531
00:24:20,401 --> 00:24:21,841
Unless they're connected.

532
00:24:23,401 --> 00:24:26,041
Your witch-hunt's
been going on a while now.

533
00:24:26,161 --> 00:24:28,841
So there's no way that mud
has just rocked up today.

534
00:24:29,601 --> 00:24:30,601
What do you know, Becka?

535
00:24:31,281 --> 00:24:33,401
What's going on here in Bilehurst Cragg?

536
00:24:34,481 --> 00:24:37,281
A woman who keeps an axe by her bed.
What have you seen?

537
00:24:39,641 --> 00:24:43,481
I have seen you with your wand,
raising your kin from the dead.

538
00:24:45,081 --> 00:24:46,361
-Yes.
-What? No.

539
00:24:46,481 --> 00:24:49,281
-Hold on a sec.
-You're no witchfinder's assistant.

540
00:24:49,481 --> 00:24:51,721
-You are Satan's acolyte!
-DOCTOR: I am not.

541
00:24:51,881 --> 00:24:54,161
That's why it's happening today,
because you are here.

542
00:24:54,281 --> 00:24:56,561
As you say, to take over this village.

543
00:24:56,681 --> 00:24:58,361
You know that's not what I meant.

544
00:24:58,481 --> 00:25:00,001
-We do not have time for this.
-(BLADE CLICKS)

545
00:25:00,481 --> 00:25:02,121
Mistress Savage is correct.

546
00:25:02,241 --> 00:25:04,401
It is your fault that Alfonso is dead.

547
00:25:04,561 --> 00:25:07,441
-I tried to save him.
-Save them

548
00:25:07,521 --> 00:25:08,881
from being shot?

549
00:25:09,041 --> 00:25:12,121
You said this evil fell from heavens.

550
00:25:12,201 --> 00:25:15,681
Oh yes, it fell,
like your lord, Lucifer!

551
00:25:15,881 --> 00:25:17,481
Honestly, if I was still a bloke,

552
00:25:17,561 --> 00:25:20,441
I could get on with the job and not
have to waste time defending myself.

553
00:25:20,521 --> 00:25:23,081
Oh, you bewitch us
with your alluring form

554
00:25:23,161 --> 00:25:24,401
and your incessant jabber,

555
00:25:24,481 --> 00:25:26,921
but I knew you were unnatural
from the very start.

556
00:25:27,521 --> 00:25:30,241
And now I see you
for what you really are.

557
00:25:30,321 --> 00:25:32,561
She was trying to save us, Sire.

558
00:25:32,641 --> 00:25:33,641
Thank you, Willa.

559
00:25:33,721 --> 00:25:35,601
BECKA: Are you sure
you're not mistaken, Willa?

560
00:25:35,681 --> 00:25:38,121
Or are you in league
with the witches as I first suspected?

561
00:25:38,201 --> 00:25:40,161
She said she wanted to help me.

562
00:25:40,241 --> 00:25:41,841
Who do you trust to save you?

563
00:25:42,041 --> 00:25:44,361
Your king? Your family?

564
00:25:44,761 --> 00:25:48,361
Whatever I have done,
I did to save all of our souls.

565
00:25:48,801 --> 00:25:50,081
What's really going on, Becka?

566
00:25:50,561 --> 00:25:52,121
Hold your tongue or I will cut it out.

567
00:25:54,841 --> 00:25:55,841
Well?

568
00:25:56,841 --> 00:25:59,121
Tell the truth, lassie.

569
00:26:07,161 --> 00:26:12,041
I did think it was strange when
they said her name was "the Doctor".

570
00:26:12,401 --> 00:26:15,121
Like Dr D, a necromancer.

571
00:26:15,521 --> 00:26:16,801
That seals it.

572
00:26:17,481 --> 00:26:18,721
Arrest the witch!

573
00:26:19,281 --> 00:26:22,361
I...I am not a witch!

574
00:26:22,441 --> 00:26:24,081
GRAHAM: Which way
do you reckon they went?

575
00:26:28,601 --> 00:26:30,361
Hey, guys, over here.

576
00:26:32,361 --> 00:26:33,441
There you go.

577
00:26:34,441 --> 00:26:35,601
Holly berries.

578
00:26:35,841 --> 00:26:37,161
No holly tree.

579
00:26:42,041 --> 00:26:44,761
YASMIN: There's more this way.
They can't be that far ahead.

580
00:26:45,161 --> 00:26:46,281
Come on.

581
00:26:53,721 --> 00:26:55,361
KING JAMES: Comfortable, witch?

582
00:26:56,001 --> 00:26:57,281
I do hope not.

583
00:26:59,721 --> 00:27:00,721
Come for a visit?

584
00:27:03,961 --> 00:27:07,761
I shall take my opportunity
to converse with an agent of Satan.

585
00:27:08,001 --> 00:27:11,201
If I was Satan's agent, do you seriously
think a bit of rope would stop me?

586
00:27:11,281 --> 00:27:13,161
I say a bit, quite a lot.

587
00:27:13,281 --> 00:27:14,441
Tightly bound.

588
00:27:14,601 --> 00:27:15,601
It's pretty painful.

589
00:27:15,681 --> 00:27:17,281
You know how to tie a knot
in this part of the world.

590
00:27:17,361 --> 00:27:20,721
I am an expert on witchcraft, Doctor.

591
00:27:21,601 --> 00:27:23,361
But I wish to learn more.

592
00:27:24,921 --> 00:27:27,881
Before you die, I want answers.

593
00:27:28,921 --> 00:27:31,321
Your wand, how does it work?

594
00:27:32,121 --> 00:27:33,281
Why do you want to know?

595
00:27:34,561 --> 00:27:36,801
I wish to know all the secrets
of existence.

596
00:27:36,921 --> 00:27:37,921
DOCTOR: Don't we all?

597
00:27:38,601 --> 00:27:40,961
But true knowledge has to be earned.

598
00:27:42,921 --> 00:27:43,961
I tell you what,

599
00:27:44,281 --> 00:27:47,241
I'll trade you my wand for answers
to as many questions you want to ask.

600
00:27:47,481 --> 00:27:48,481
(SCOFFS)

601
00:27:49,241 --> 00:27:50,761
I'm not a fool, Doctor.

602
00:27:52,001 --> 00:27:56,001
-I am King James, Satan's greatest foe.
-DOCTOR: Yeah, yeah. I know.

603
00:27:56,281 --> 00:27:58,321
It must be comforting,
playing that role.

604
00:27:58,961 --> 00:28:00,441
Hiding behind a title.

605
00:28:01,441 --> 00:28:04,761
Just as you hide behind
"Doctor”, perhaps.

606
00:28:08,401 --> 00:28:09,401
(INDISTINCT WHISPERING)

607
00:28:09,481 --> 00:28:11,321
You should take up witch finding
for a living.

608
00:28:11,601 --> 00:28:12,601
Yeah.

609
00:28:13,161 --> 00:28:16,041
Shame I missed the training session
on what to do when you found them.

610
00:28:17,241 --> 00:28:18,801
RYAN: I guess we have to follow them

611
00:28:19,281 --> 00:28:20,441
very quietly.

612
00:28:20,721 --> 00:28:21,721
Okay.

613
00:28:24,321 --> 00:28:25,521
Who are you, really?

614
00:28:25,841 --> 00:28:27,041
Behind the mask?

615
00:28:27,521 --> 00:28:29,041
The drama?

616
00:28:29,961 --> 00:28:31,881
What does it say on your garter?

617
00:28:31,961 --> 00:28:33,401
"Honi soit gqui mal y pense.”

618
00:28:33,481 --> 00:28:35,241
"Evil be to him that evil thinks."

619
00:28:36,521 --> 00:28:38,161
You wear it like a hero,

620
00:28:38,241 --> 00:28:41,001
even though you're killing
and scapegoating,

621
00:28:41,441 --> 00:28:42,881
and stirring up hate.

622
00:28:43,841 --> 00:28:46,161
And you wonder why the darkness
comes back at you.

623
00:28:46,281 --> 00:28:47,681
There's no darkness in me.

624
00:28:48,721 --> 00:28:53,561
I quest for goodness and knowledge,
beauty and art, all of God's virtues.

625
00:28:53,641 --> 00:28:55,041
Your own mother was scapegoated.

626
00:28:55,281 --> 00:28:57,001
How do you square that
with your witch-hunts?

627
00:28:57,081 --> 00:28:58,561
What do you know of my mother?

628
00:28:59,441 --> 00:29:01,441
You could have seen her before she died,

629
00:29:01,561 --> 00:29:03,041
but you didn't want to, why?

630
00:29:03,521 --> 00:29:04,921
She left me

631
00:29:06,961 --> 00:29:09,441
when I was not even one year old.

632
00:29:09,561 --> 00:29:11,281
What kind of mother does that?

633
00:29:11,561 --> 00:29:13,001
Why would I wish to see her?

634
00:29:13,361 --> 00:29:15,881
Nobody will ever know
why she left you, James.

635
00:29:16,201 --> 00:29:19,401
But you can't go hurting people
just because you're scared

636
00:29:19,481 --> 00:29:21,681
to face up to the darkness inside you.

637
00:29:21,841 --> 00:29:23,561
You have to be better than that.

638
00:29:28,001 --> 00:29:29,081
Who are you?

639
00:29:31,201 --> 00:29:32,521
How do you know these things?

640
00:29:32,921 --> 00:29:33,961
I know because

641
00:29:34,681 --> 00:29:36,121
we are all the same.

642
00:29:37,161 --> 00:29:40,481
We want certainty, security.

643
00:29:40,561 --> 00:29:43,601
To believe that people are evil
or heroic.

644
00:29:43,721 --> 00:29:45,681
But that's not how people are.

645
00:29:45,801 --> 00:29:48,481
You want to know
the secrets of existence?

646
00:29:49,361 --> 00:29:51,761
Start with the mysteries of the heart.

647
00:29:53,561 --> 00:29:55,401
I can show you everything

648
00:29:55,481 --> 00:29:58,761
if you stop being afraid
of what you don't understand.

649
00:29:58,841 --> 00:30:00,081
If you trust me.

650
00:30:02,481 --> 00:30:03,761
I am not a witch.

651
00:30:05,401 --> 00:30:09,321
But if you want to defeat evil,
you have to let me go. Now.

652
00:30:10,081 --> 00:30:12,081
Please, Sire.

653
00:30:15,481 --> 00:30:17,401
(DOCTOR BREATHING HEAVILY)

654
00:30:19,601 --> 00:30:21,481
I do not know what you are,

655
00:30:23,641 --> 00:30:26,041
and there is only one way to be certain.

656
00:30:26,161 --> 00:30:28,761
Guards, summon the villagers!

657
00:30:30,801 --> 00:30:32,841
RYAN: All the way through the forest
and back where we started.

658
00:30:32,921 --> 00:30:34,361
GRAHAM: Keep your voice down.

659
00:30:34,441 --> 00:30:36,241
YASMIN: What would they come here for?

660
00:30:36,321 --> 00:30:38,041
(LIQUID BUBBLING)

661
00:30:38,121 --> 00:30:39,441
(EXHALES)

662
00:30:40,001 --> 00:30:41,401
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

663
00:30:44,761 --> 00:30:45,921
That's Becka's bedroom.

664
00:30:46,801 --> 00:30:47,801
They're looking for her.

665
00:30:47,921 --> 00:30:49,801
Revenge, that's why the undead
always come back.

666
00:30:49,921 --> 00:30:51,041
Must be why Becka has the axe.

667
00:30:51,121 --> 00:30:52,201
(AXE CLANKING)

668
00:30:52,321 --> 00:30:53,521
GRAHAM: Speaking of which.

669
00:30:53,601 --> 00:30:54,601
In here.

670
00:31:00,681 --> 00:31:01,961
RYAN: Where are they going now?

671
00:31:08,441 --> 00:31:09,561
-(HAND BELL RINGING)
-DOCTOR: I see you've

672
00:31:09,641 --> 00:31:10,681
brought a gathering.

673
00:31:10,761 --> 00:31:12,201
Thanks very much.

674
00:31:14,881 --> 00:31:16,081
Mind if I take off my coat?

675
00:31:16,481 --> 00:31:17,561
Lots in my pockets.

676
00:31:17,881 --> 00:31:19,041
Might stop me floating.

677
00:31:19,321 --> 00:31:21,441
Of course, as a woman, you don't get
to have pockets for a while yet.

678
00:31:22,641 --> 00:31:25,281
A girl called Izzy Flint
bullied my friend Yaz

679
00:31:25,561 --> 00:31:26,961
so no one would pick on Izzy.

680
00:31:27,641 --> 00:31:28,761
That's what you're doing.

681
00:31:29,001 --> 00:31:31,681
Pointing the finger at other people
so no one points it at you.

682
00:31:31,761 --> 00:31:35,481
But what I don't know is, why?
What are you hiding, Becka?

683
00:31:35,601 --> 00:31:36,841
Sit down.

684
00:31:37,321 --> 00:31:38,961
Or would you prefer a hanging?

685
00:31:39,041 --> 00:31:40,401
(CHAINS RATTLING)

686
00:31:43,001 --> 00:31:45,441
Do you know why the ducking stool
was invented, Doctor?

687
00:31:46,401 --> 00:31:48,761
To silence foolish women
who talk too much.

688
00:31:48,921 --> 00:31:51,561
Yeah, I did know that, which is daft,
because talking's brilliant.

689
00:31:51,641 --> 00:31:54,081
Like, if you'd talk to me now,
I can help.

690
00:31:54,321 --> 00:31:57,321
You've ducked 36 people already.

691
00:31:57,641 --> 00:32:00,001
And whatever it is has only got worse,
hasn't it?

692
00:32:00,081 --> 00:32:01,321
(CRACKLES)

693
00:32:03,281 --> 00:32:04,321
What was that?

694
00:32:05,641 --> 00:32:06,841
It reacted to your touch, why?

695
00:32:07,681 --> 00:32:08,801
I warned you to keep quiet.

696
00:32:08,881 --> 00:32:10,121
-Rather I ask Willa?
-Silence!

697
00:32:11,081 --> 00:32:12,481
Or I shall duck her, too.

698
00:32:12,961 --> 00:32:14,681
Last request.
I definitely get a last request.

699
00:32:14,881 --> 00:32:15,881
(CHAINS CLINK)

700
00:32:16,881 --> 00:32:17,881
Lend us your hanky.

701
00:32:19,561 --> 00:32:20,561
I don't have one.

702
00:32:20,841 --> 00:32:21,961
There's loads in your room.

703
00:32:22,401 --> 00:32:23,681
And an empty medicine bottle.

704
00:32:23,801 --> 00:32:25,561
What were you taking
the medicine for, Becka?

705
00:32:25,841 --> 00:32:27,081
Know this, Doctor,

706
00:32:27,521 --> 00:32:31,321
once I have dealt with you,
I shall go after all of your friends.

707
00:32:33,721 --> 00:32:34,721
RYAN: Quiet a sec.

708
00:32:35,161 --> 00:32:36,161
(HAND BELL RINGING IN DISTANCE)

709
00:32:36,241 --> 00:32:37,361
Listen.

710
00:32:38,841 --> 00:32:40,081
That was coming from the river.

711
00:32:41,321 --> 00:32:42,441
Someone must be getting ducked.

712
00:32:42,521 --> 00:32:44,081
The Doctor wouldn't let that happen.

713
00:32:44,281 --> 00:32:45,681
-Oh.
-Unless...

714
00:32:45,841 --> 00:32:47,321
-Yeah.
-BECKA: Satan has made

715
00:32:47,401 --> 00:32:51,561
our crops fail, bewitched our animals,
and brought the sickness.

716
00:32:52,521 --> 00:32:54,241
His agent sits before you.

717
00:32:54,681 --> 00:32:56,881
The most evil witch in Christendom.

718
00:32:56,961 --> 00:32:59,681
And she would call herself "the Doctor".

719
00:32:59,761 --> 00:33:00,761
(VILLAGERS JEERING)

720
00:33:01,601 --> 00:33:05,561
We bring her to justice
in front of our great Majesty,

721
00:33:05,641 --> 00:33:06,841
King James.

722
00:33:06,921 --> 00:33:09,001
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)
-Give the word, Sire,

723
00:33:09,081 --> 00:33:11,241
and we shall duck the witch

724
00:33:11,321 --> 00:33:13,121
and save our souls from Satan

725
00:33:14,801 --> 00:33:16,441
once and for all.

726
00:33:17,681 --> 00:33:19,281
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

727
00:33:20,801 --> 00:33:21,801
-Duck the witch.
-MAN: Duck her!

728
00:33:22,121 --> 00:33:23,721
(VILLAGERS CLAMOURING)

729
00:33:25,521 --> 00:33:26,521
I was right.

730
00:33:26,601 --> 00:33:29,081
-Doctor!
-BECKA: Guards, duck her now.

731
00:33:32,001 --> 00:33:34,641
-Bring her back up now.
-RYAN: What have you done?

732
00:33:34,721 --> 00:33:35,721
You will see the result.

733
00:33:35,801 --> 00:33:38,241
I'm the Witchfinder General,
I'm giving you an order.

734
00:33:38,321 --> 00:33:39,561
I obey only my king.

735
00:33:39,681 --> 00:33:41,161
Sire, please order her to be raised.

736
00:33:41,241 --> 00:33:43,761
She's not a witch, she's your only hope
of getting out of here alive.

737
00:33:43,881 --> 00:33:45,401
BECKA: They're witches, Sire.

738
00:33:45,481 --> 00:33:48,081
All of them. It's Satan testing us.

739
00:33:48,281 --> 00:33:49,601
YASMIN: Get her out of there.

740
00:33:49,881 --> 00:33:50,921
It has been long enough.

741
00:33:51,001 --> 00:33:53,401
No, it hasn't. We must be certain.

742
00:33:53,641 --> 00:33:54,641
Bring her up, now.

743
00:33:56,361 --> 00:33:57,361
Now!

744
00:33:57,601 --> 00:33:58,721
RYAN: Please, Your Majesty.

745
00:34:00,521 --> 00:34:03,121
Raise the stool. The trial is over.

746
00:34:06,201 --> 00:34:08,681
RYAN: Where has she gone?
What's happened to her?

747
00:34:09,321 --> 00:34:10,441
No.

748
00:34:11,041 --> 00:34:12,201
No!

749
00:34:15,561 --> 00:34:16,561
YASMIN: Where is she?

750
00:34:16,801 --> 00:34:18,721
-Looking for me?
-YASMIN: Doctor!

751
00:34:20,401 --> 00:34:22,121
She truly is a powerful witch.

752
00:34:22,241 --> 00:34:24,201
No, Sire, I am no witch.

753
00:34:25,041 --> 00:34:26,401
I'm just good at holding my breath

754
00:34:26,481 --> 00:34:27,921
and getting out of chains

755
00:34:28,001 --> 00:34:29,961
thanks to a very wet weekend
with Houdini.

756
00:34:30,601 --> 00:34:31,761
Hi, team.

757
00:34:32,001 --> 00:34:33,841
Gang. Fam!

758
00:34:35,041 --> 00:34:37,161
-No.
-WILLA: I'm so sorry, Doctor.

759
00:34:37,241 --> 00:34:38,481
I was scared.

760
00:34:38,761 --> 00:34:39,761
See?

761
00:34:39,961 --> 00:34:41,201
That's all it takes, Becka.

762
00:34:41,641 --> 00:34:42,761
Start there.

763
00:34:43,161 --> 00:34:44,961
Tell me the truth.

764
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:47,921
(BREATHING HEAVILY)
She survived, she is a witch!

765
00:34:48,041 --> 00:34:49,401
No, I'm not.

766
00:34:49,961 --> 00:34:52,441
-And despite all appearances...
-WILLA: Doctor!

767
00:34:52,521 --> 00:34:53,521
...neither are they.

768
00:34:54,161 --> 00:34:56,361
You might want to come and stand
with me now, Becka,

769
00:34:56,441 --> 00:34:58,281
'cause they look like
they've come for you.

770
00:34:58,361 --> 00:34:59,441
(VILLAGERS SCREAMING)

771
00:35:00,321 --> 00:35:01,921
(MUTTERING)

772
00:35:02,441 --> 00:35:03,481
RYAN: We have to help out.

773
00:35:03,681 --> 00:35:05,961
Yes. Yes, we must confront those agents

774
00:35:06,201 --> 00:35:08,161
of Satan even in the face
of witchery and...

775
00:35:08,321 --> 00:35:12,121
Oh, mate, seriously? Not witches.
Bodies, possessed by alien mud.

776
00:35:12,401 --> 00:35:13,401
Come on!

777
00:35:14,121 --> 00:35:15,521
I will be with you.

778
00:35:15,961 --> 00:35:17,041
In the water.

779
00:35:17,721 --> 00:35:19,041
In the fire.

780
00:35:19,321 --> 00:35:20,561
In the air.

781
00:35:20,641 --> 00:35:21,881
Stop, just stop.

782
00:35:23,841 --> 00:35:25,841
They're obeying you.
Why are they obeying you?

783
00:35:25,921 --> 00:35:27,321
What happened, Becka?

784
00:35:27,401 --> 00:35:28,801
I thought they'd come to kill you.

785
00:35:28,881 --> 00:35:31,921
Which is a fair assumption
given they're carrying an axe.

786
00:35:32,001 --> 00:35:33,121
But they haven't, have they?

787
00:35:33,601 --> 00:35:36,041
Of course, they've come to join you.

788
00:35:36,481 --> 00:35:37,761
(COUGHING AND GASPING)

789
00:35:37,961 --> 00:35:40,481
It's in you, just as it's in them.

790
00:35:40,641 --> 00:35:42,361
And none of you can hide it any more.

791
00:35:42,521 --> 00:35:43,521
In the earth.

792
00:35:43,601 --> 00:35:44,601
What happened?

793
00:35:45,361 --> 00:35:47,081
I cut down her favourite tree.

794
00:35:47,161 --> 00:35:48,321
(SNARLS)

795
00:35:48,401 --> 00:35:49,881
What? I don't understand.

796
00:35:51,001 --> 00:35:53,601
BECKA: It was spoiling
my view of the hill.

797
00:35:53,681 --> 00:35:54,801
(GRUNTING)

798
00:35:59,601 --> 00:36:01,441
But something lay beneath it.

799
00:36:02,401 --> 00:36:04,401
I awoke hell

800
00:36:04,481 --> 00:36:06,761
Satan himself attacked me,

801
00:36:06,841 --> 00:36:08,201
poisoned me.

802
00:36:08,881 --> 00:36:11,201
That night, I felt it growing inside me.

803
00:36:11,641 --> 00:36:13,281
The mark of Satan.

804
00:36:14,121 --> 00:36:15,441
I fought it.

805
00:36:16,041 --> 00:36:18,201
I took medicine, I prayed.

806
00:36:18,481 --> 00:36:22,761
But it grew. I did God's work
in the hope that he would save me.

807
00:36:22,881 --> 00:36:25,921
You killed people
to try and save yourself.

808
00:36:26,001 --> 00:36:28,681
All these witches? All this evil?

809
00:36:28,801 --> 00:36:30,161
You knew they weren't witches.

810
00:36:30,601 --> 00:36:33,041
The only thing you feared was yourself.

811
00:36:33,961 --> 00:36:35,801
Did your granny know
what you needed the medicine for?

812
00:36:35,921 --> 00:36:38,521
Not to start with,
but then I had to tell her.

813
00:36:39,441 --> 00:36:41,601
I needed her help. I begged for it.

814
00:36:42,041 --> 00:36:45,001
For her to lance this evil out of me!
(SOBBING)

815
00:36:47,241 --> 00:36:49,161
But she was too weak.

816
00:36:50,961 --> 00:36:52,441
So you killed her by ducking?

817
00:36:52,601 --> 00:36:54,041
I had to, she knew!

818
00:36:54,161 --> 00:36:55,241
-(MUD FLOWING)
-(GROANING)

819
00:36:56,001 --> 00:36:58,121
I can't fight it any more, Doctor.

820
00:36:58,321 --> 00:37:00,561
You cannot fight it
because you are the witch.

821
00:37:00,881 --> 00:37:02,641
I have let Satan in.

822
00:37:03,241 --> 00:37:04,841
I have failed you, Sire.

823
00:37:04,921 --> 00:37:07,041
Yes, I am the witch!

824
00:37:07,241 --> 00:37:08,481
Everyone, behind me.

825
00:37:08,641 --> 00:37:10,121
-It's Becka they want.
-RYAN: But why?

826
00:37:10,721 --> 00:37:12,001
WILLA: What's happening to her?

827
00:37:12,081 --> 00:37:14,001
I tried to hold Satan back.

828
00:37:14,841 --> 00:37:16,761
I'm so scared.

829
00:37:16,841 --> 00:37:18,881
Please forgive me!

830
00:37:18,961 --> 00:37:19,961
(GASPS)

831
00:37:21,801 --> 00:37:23,801
(DEMONIC SCREAMING)

832
00:37:25,681 --> 00:37:26,681
What is happening?

833
00:37:27,681 --> 00:37:29,481
She's possessed by Satan.

834
00:37:29,641 --> 00:37:30,721
Not by Satan.

835
00:37:32,001 --> 00:37:33,001
Then by what?

836
00:37:34,401 --> 00:37:35,481
Something not of this Earth.

837
00:37:36,041 --> 00:37:37,921
(BIRDS SQUAWKING)

838
00:37:38,161 --> 00:37:39,281
Morax.

839
00:37:41,881 --> 00:37:42,961
Who are you?

840
00:37:43,041 --> 00:37:44,801
Hand me your king.

841
00:37:45,081 --> 00:37:47,121
-What?
-Haven't you got your own king?

842
00:37:47,201 --> 00:37:49,761
-Or is he hiding?
-He does not hide.

843
00:37:50,081 --> 00:37:51,201
He waits.

844
00:37:51,401 --> 00:37:55,601
We have all waited for too long,
trapped in the hill.

845
00:37:56,241 --> 00:37:58,161
-Pendle Hill.
-MORAX: Our prison.

846
00:37:58,561 --> 00:38:00,721
The mighty Morax army,

847
00:38:01,201 --> 00:38:04,921
captured and imprisoned
on this pitiful planet

848
00:38:05,081 --> 00:38:06,921
for war crimes.

849
00:38:07,041 --> 00:38:10,481
Pendle Hill is a prison
for an alien army!

850
00:38:10,761 --> 00:38:12,841
Oh, well, it's obvious
when you put it like that.

851
00:38:12,961 --> 00:38:16,281
Imprisoned no more. The lock was broken.

852
00:38:16,361 --> 00:38:18,401
What lock? How was it broken?

853
00:38:18,561 --> 00:38:22,321
Now, the Morax army shall rise again

854
00:38:22,401 --> 00:38:24,001
and take form.

855
00:38:24,441 --> 00:38:27,241
Your king shall be filled with our king,

856
00:38:27,441 --> 00:38:31,201
and we shall be free to fill all of you.

857
00:38:32,001 --> 00:38:36,081
To fill this whole planet with rage

858
00:38:36,161 --> 00:38:38,321
and force, and hate,

859
00:38:38,881 --> 00:38:40,361
and Morax!

860
00:38:43,121 --> 00:38:44,361
YASMIN: Come on, Witchfinder.

861
00:38:46,081 --> 00:38:47,081
Up you get.

862
00:38:48,241 --> 00:38:49,241
Go on, what happened?

863
00:38:49,321 --> 00:38:50,721
YASMIN: Same thing happened
to all of us.

864
00:38:50,841 --> 00:38:52,081
Oh, ow.

865
00:38:52,321 --> 00:38:54,361
Zapped by Becka Savage,
queen of the Morax.

866
00:38:54,481 --> 00:38:56,601
-(GROANING)
-She's taken the king,

867
00:38:56,681 --> 00:38:58,001
-knocked the rest of us out.
-(GROANS) Okay.

868
00:38:58,201 --> 00:38:59,361
DOCTOR: Quite a blast, that.

869
00:38:59,441 --> 00:39:02,281
Haven't had a hangover like this
since the Milk Wars of Keston Five.

870
00:39:02,361 --> 00:39:03,441
What are you doing with this thing?

871
00:39:03,721 --> 00:39:05,961
Tell them what "Bilehurst" means.

872
00:39:06,241 --> 00:39:07,481
Sacred tree on a hill.

873
00:39:07,561 --> 00:39:10,001
The tree Becka chopped down
because it was obscuring her view,

874
00:39:10,121 --> 00:39:12,601
the tree this ducking stool
is made from,

875
00:39:12,721 --> 00:39:14,121
the tree that isn't a tree...

876
00:39:14,401 --> 00:39:18,041
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-...is ancient alien technology.

877
00:39:18,241 --> 00:39:20,601
Beautiful and broken.

878
00:39:20,841 --> 00:39:24,361
A very old, very advanced,
biomech security system.

879
00:39:24,441 --> 00:39:27,801
A lock to keep the Morax army
imprisoned here.

880
00:39:28,081 --> 00:39:31,561
It responded to Becka's touch because
of the Morax infection inside her.

881
00:39:31,721 --> 00:39:33,081
So, Pendle Hill was a prison?

882
00:39:33,161 --> 00:39:35,761
From what Becka said,
I'm guessing the Morax

883
00:39:35,841 --> 00:39:39,401
are royals with soldiers,
pretty brutal ones at that.

884
00:39:39,481 --> 00:39:42,001
Presumably exiled for war crimes,

885
00:39:42,121 --> 00:39:44,081
scrambled down into their primal form...

886
00:39:44,161 --> 00:39:47,041
And they stay in prison
until Becka Savage goes at that tree.

887
00:39:47,161 --> 00:39:49,281
Well, it can't be much of a lock
if she can break it.

888
00:39:49,361 --> 00:39:53,521
It's old. Eroded over billions
of years, presumably.

889
00:39:54,041 --> 00:39:55,961
But she must have broke it enough

890
00:39:56,041 --> 00:39:59,081
for part of the queen's form
to escape and infect her.

891
00:39:59,161 --> 00:40:02,081
According to my calculations,
this ancient alien wood

892
00:40:02,161 --> 00:40:03,721
is like Semtex to Morax.

893
00:40:03,841 --> 00:40:05,761
That's why it made such a good lock.

894
00:40:05,841 --> 00:40:07,601
Right, help me break it up.

895
00:40:08,041 --> 00:40:09,601
Break it up? Why, what for?

896
00:40:09,761 --> 00:40:10,761
(WOOD CRACKING)

897
00:40:11,681 --> 00:40:13,201
Anti-Morax weapons.

898
00:40:13,321 --> 00:40:15,081
The smoke is toxic to Morax.

899
00:40:15,321 --> 00:40:16,481
Should be enough to fend them off

900
00:40:16,561 --> 00:40:18,681
so you can rescue King James
and I can get to the tree.

901
00:40:18,761 --> 00:40:19,761
Then what?

902
00:40:19,881 --> 00:40:21,201
-(SONIC SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-I fix the lock,

903
00:40:21,281 --> 00:40:23,201
putting all the Morax energy
back in the slammer.

904
00:40:23,561 --> 00:40:24,561
GRAHAM: One more thing, Doc.

905
00:40:28,881 --> 00:40:30,961
Moraxfinder General back in command.

906
00:40:31,921 --> 00:40:33,241
It's a very flat team structure.

907
00:40:35,241 --> 00:40:36,401
Ready for battle?

908
00:40:36,841 --> 00:40:37,841
Yes, we are.

909
00:40:38,881 --> 00:40:39,921
You don't have to, Willa.

910
00:40:40,721 --> 00:40:41,961
It's time to stop being scared.

911
00:40:42,321 --> 00:40:43,641
Little bit of scared isn't a bad thing.

912
00:40:44,241 --> 00:40:46,321
Morax is way more dangerous
than Becka ever was.

913
00:40:46,401 --> 00:40:48,041
Only I know the path up the hill.

914
00:40:48,681 --> 00:40:50,121
So you need me to lead the way.

915
00:40:50,201 --> 00:40:51,201
She's right, Doc.

916
00:40:52,121 --> 00:40:54,481
There are more powerful people here
than kings and queens.

917
00:40:55,681 --> 00:40:56,681
There's us.

918
00:40:57,641 --> 00:40:58,641
Together.

919
00:41:00,801 --> 00:41:02,281
Lead on, Willa Twiston.

920
00:41:06,001 --> 00:41:08,401
Onwards, to save the king.

921
00:41:09,321 --> 00:41:12,121
MORAX: Kneel before Morax, feeble human.

922
00:41:12,201 --> 00:41:14,801
Tell me what you are,
you Satanic creature.

923
00:41:15,241 --> 00:41:17,721
-We will rule this world.
-KING JAMES: "We"?

924
00:41:17,801 --> 00:41:21,001
Your body filled with my Morax king.

925
00:41:21,521 --> 00:41:23,481
Come to me, my love.

926
00:41:24,121 --> 00:41:25,121
(GASPS)

927
00:41:26,121 --> 00:41:27,121
(GASPS SOFTLY)

928
00:41:27,601 --> 00:41:29,241
KING JAMES: Satan rises.

929
00:41:29,441 --> 00:41:30,641
(JAMES GROANS)

930
00:41:31,281 --> 00:41:32,281
(JAMES SCREAMS)

931
00:41:32,601 --> 00:41:33,601
(PANTING)

932
00:41:35,201 --> 00:41:37,801
I may fear you, but I have my faith.

933
00:41:38,081 --> 00:41:39,121
(ROARS)

934
00:41:39,321 --> 00:41:40,921
May the Lord save me!

935
00:41:41,001 --> 00:41:42,121
DOCTOR: Or, alternatively,

936
00:41:42,641 --> 00:41:45,121
Witchfinders United at your service.

937
00:41:45,241 --> 00:41:47,201
Yeah, mate, you better back off.

938
00:41:47,921 --> 00:41:49,281
Let him go, Morax.

939
00:41:49,801 --> 00:41:51,161
You can't have King James

940
00:41:51,481 --> 00:41:52,481
or this planet.

941
00:41:52,801 --> 00:41:53,921
RYAN: Get away from the king.

942
00:41:54,121 --> 00:41:55,361
(GRUNTING)

943
00:41:55,521 --> 00:41:57,721
The torches are working.
He won't come near the flames.

944
00:41:57,961 --> 00:41:59,641
RYAN: I've got you, Sire.
KING JAMES: My protector!

945
00:41:59,881 --> 00:42:01,521
Willa, watch out for your granny.

946
00:42:01,641 --> 00:42:03,521
-(SNARLS)
-You're not my granny.

947
00:42:03,601 --> 00:42:04,921
Let her rest!

948
00:42:05,001 --> 00:42:07,761
And you, Morax, back into your cell.
Now, please.

949
00:42:07,841 --> 00:42:10,121
Those flames don't scare me, Doctor.

950
00:42:10,281 --> 00:42:12,041
Nothing scares me now!

951
00:42:12,281 --> 00:42:13,801
WILLA: I know you're in there, Becka.

952
00:42:14,881 --> 00:42:16,201
I know you're scared.

953
00:42:16,401 --> 00:42:19,481
Nothing of that pathetic woman remains.

954
00:42:19,601 --> 00:42:22,401
No fear, only power.

955
00:42:22,721 --> 00:42:26,641
We will fill your king and kill you all!

956
00:42:26,721 --> 00:42:28,761
Afraid not, Morax. I'm here.

957
00:42:29,161 --> 00:42:30,161
(MORAX SCREAMS)

958
00:42:30,721 --> 00:42:32,361
-DOCTOR: Everybody back!
- (EXCLAIMING)

959
00:42:32,441 --> 00:42:33,641
DOCTOR: I've reactivated the prison.

960
00:42:33,721 --> 00:42:35,921
Back you go, King of the Morax!

961
00:42:42,881 --> 00:42:44,321
(ROARING)

962
00:42:45,281 --> 00:42:46,401
DOCTOR: Jail re-energised.

963
00:42:46,601 --> 00:42:47,601
MORAX: No!

964
00:42:48,201 --> 00:42:50,201
What have you done?

965
00:42:51,081 --> 00:42:53,161
Feel that security system
kicking back in,

966
00:42:53,361 --> 00:42:55,921
sucking every Morax cell back.

967
00:42:56,641 --> 00:42:58,361
Back down into Pendle Hill.

968
00:42:58,441 --> 00:43:00,481
Back out of the bodies they hijacked.

969
00:43:02,321 --> 00:43:03,321
Have peace.

970
00:43:03,521 --> 00:43:05,121
MORAX: No!

971
00:43:05,321 --> 00:43:06,881
I will not go!

972
00:43:06,961 --> 00:43:08,081
Yes, you will.

973
00:43:08,161 --> 00:43:10,681
-Burn the witch!
-DOCTOR: No, Sire, stay away!

974
00:43:10,761 --> 00:43:12,281
(SCREAMING)

975
00:43:17,601 --> 00:43:19,361
(ALL PANTING)

976
00:43:23,721 --> 00:43:25,441
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

977
00:43:26,281 --> 00:43:29,401
What, woman?
She was a witch. She confessed.

978
00:43:29,761 --> 00:43:32,601
-So you got what you came for.
-I have vanquished Satan.

979
00:43:34,481 --> 00:43:36,201
No more witch-hunts.

980
00:43:45,681 --> 00:43:47,761
She still does not speak to me, Ryan.

981
00:43:48,121 --> 00:43:49,521
Can you get through to her?

982
00:43:49,641 --> 00:43:51,801
Afraid not, Sire. This is on you.

983
00:43:52,201 --> 00:43:53,961
What apparition is this?

984
00:43:54,561 --> 00:43:56,801
Just another inexplicable
wonder of existence

985
00:43:56,921 --> 00:43:58,881
you're not going to be able
to tell anyone about.

986
00:43:58,961 --> 00:44:01,561
Doctor, I understand
you are displeased with me.

987
00:44:02,961 --> 00:44:04,481
And I owe my life to you.

988
00:44:06,081 --> 00:44:09,401
Not one word of any of this
shall ever be spoken.

989
00:44:10,401 --> 00:44:13,361
And even the name "Bilehurst"
shall be erased

990
00:44:13,761 --> 00:44:15,081
from all records.

991
00:44:15,841 --> 00:44:17,761
As long as all the villagers
make it out alive.

992
00:44:18,401 --> 00:44:19,561
What will you do, Willa?

993
00:44:20,921 --> 00:44:21,921
Find a new home?

994
00:44:22,481 --> 00:44:25,201
Take Granny's potions and be a healer.

995
00:44:26,961 --> 00:44:28,041
Be a doctor.

996
00:44:29,561 --> 00:44:31,081
I reckon you'll be good at that.

997
00:44:31,321 --> 00:44:32,481
One final command,

998
00:44:33,601 --> 00:44:34,961
as your king.

999
00:44:37,001 --> 00:44:38,641
Come back to London with me, Ryan.

1000
00:44:40,561 --> 00:44:41,761
Be my protector.

1001
00:44:46,361 --> 00:44:47,641
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY) I mean,

1002
00:44:48,321 --> 00:44:50,041
it's a kind offer, Sire,

1003
00:44:50,401 --> 00:44:52,041
but, er, you know,

1004
00:44:52,681 --> 00:44:53,761
I've got stuff to do.

1005
00:44:54,761 --> 00:44:58,441
But I'll keep me eye on you.

1006
00:44:59,281 --> 00:45:02,521
So you behave yourself. (CHUCKLES)

1007
00:45:03,841 --> 00:45:05,001
(LAUGHS)

1008
00:45:05,601 --> 00:45:06,721
Or else...

1009
00:45:07,401 --> 00:45:09,921
-(TARDIS DOOR OPENS)
-...we will strike down upon thee

1010
00:45:10,001 --> 00:45:13,681
with great vengeance and furious anger.

1011
00:45:14,041 --> 00:45:15,041
Ezekiel.

1012
00:45:15,241 --> 00:45:16,241
Tarantino.

1013
00:45:18,041 --> 00:45:19,641
Wh... What are you all doing?

1014
00:45:20,121 --> 00:45:21,361
A brilliant man once said,

1015
00:45:22,041 --> 00:45:25,601
"Any sufficiently advanced technology
is indistinguishable from magic.”

1016
00:45:28,241 --> 00:45:29,761
We're just about to prove him right.

1017
00:45:31,881 --> 00:45:32,921
(TARDIS DOOR CLOSES)

1018
00:45:34,841 --> 00:45:36,921
(WHOOSHING)

1019
00:45:41,481 --> 00:45:43,241
Where did they go?

1020
00:45:44,521 --> 00:45:46,121
(LAUGHS)

1021
00:45:49,721 --> 00:45:51,521
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

1022
00:46:19,521 --> 00:46:23,721
DOCTOR: A cottage in Norway in winter,
with a chimney but no smoke.

1023
00:46:24,081 --> 00:46:25,361
MAN'S VOICE: Such tragedy

1024
00:46:26,081 --> 00:46:27,161
makes me

1025
00:46:27,761 --> 00:46:29,081
hungry.

